---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Resource Library"
  description="A searchable library of downloadable problem gambling prevention resources — rack cards, fact sheets, graphics, and more, customized by state."
>
  <header class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="page-header__eyebrow">Resource Library</p>
      <h1>Resources to download and use</h1>
      <p class="page-header__lead">
        A growing library of problem gambling prevention materials — for
        non-commercial prevention and education.
      </p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <h2>What's coming</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Rack cards</strong> — print-ready, customized with each state's helpline and context</li>
        <li><strong>Fact sheets</strong> — one-page overviews of key topics</li>
        <li><strong>Social-media graphics</strong> — sized for major platforms</li>
        <li><strong>Presentation slide decks</strong> — editable, for community presentations</li>
        <li><strong>Infographics</strong> — data-driven visuals with cited sources</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How you'll find what you need</h2>
      <p>You'll be able to filter the library by:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>State or territory</li>
        <li>IC&amp;RC Prevention Specialist domain</li>
        <li>CSAP prevention strategy</li>
        <li>Audience (general public, youth, young adults, parents, providers, policymakers, older adults)</li>
        <li>Resource type</li>
        <li>Topic (sports betting, online gambling, youth, families, suicide risk, and more)</li>
        <li>Language</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>In the meantime</h2>
      <p>
        The <a href="/understand-gambling">Understand Gambling</a> pages can be
        shared and used today, and the <a href="/professionals">professional hub</a>
        is organized by IC&amp;RC PS domain. Every <a href="/find-your-state">state
        page</a> already carries local helpline, regulator, and legal-landscape
        information you can cite.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
